layers.nm: I was born in 1989, and raised in Latakia-Syria on the coast of the Mediterranean sea, I graduated with a Bachelor degree from Tishreen University in the year 2013, I worked during my studies on a wide array of projects, ranging from interiors to mid-sized touristic projects, and realized that I'm very interested in design, 3D modeling, and visualisation.

layers.nm: I moved to Russia in 2013, to continue my studies in Architecture, and collaborated with several moscow based architects, I designed interiors, exteriors, and participated in the design of a public park, working in Russia was a very valuable opportunity to me, as my first working abroad experience.

layers.nm: I was briefly in Norway, and during my time there, i did a short internship, and designed 2 small vacation huts for one client, I learned a lot during this time, and grew to appreciate Nordic architecture and design school.

layers.nm: I live in Germany since the beginning of 2016, I started my career here with an internship to get familiar with German architecture practices and workflow, after that i got my first full time job here, as a motion and graphic designer in a film agency, where i participated in numerous projects for big names, created many 2D and 3D animation, and managed small projects from A to Z, and since 2018, I work as an architect-3D artist at Werner Sobek Design, my tasks here range from designing to visualising high profile projects, participating in competitions, communicating and collaborating with an international team on projects scattered all over the  world.
